    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, which is acceptable per ASME V&V 40 at Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model predicts RH index within 8.3% mean error against FDA benchmark experimental data across all 5 operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The model employs a simplified steady-state Newtonian formulation; the validation activities are structured to match this formulation, and agreement is deemed adequate for the intended regulatory decision. The credibility package is accepted to support submission of the Class II CPB device.",
